3.1: Each Umamusume has different goals. \nLet's now work to realize these goals!
3.2: These are the commands that let you \nadvance through training.
3.3: Executing one command consumes a turn.
3.4: Let's go with the actual "Training" first!
3.5: These are the types of training available! \nEach one improves different capabilities.
3.6: Let's see what happens when we choose "Speed"!
3.7: Now, I want to talk to you about your \nUmamusume's energy when training.
3.8: First, as before, let's choose a training.
3.9: Please pay attention to the "failure rate" here.
3.10: The less energy you have left, the higher the \nfailure rate will be.
3.11: Failing a training will reduce capabilities and \nmotivation so be careful…!
3.12: Now, let's get back to it.
3.13: When your Umamusume's energy is low, \nlet her take a rest to recover.
3.15: Next, choose a skill to learn. \nWe'll use the skill points you just earned!
3.16: Let's have her learn this skill for now.
3.18: And we're all set! \nLet's enter a race!
3.19: When there is a race that she can run, \nit will show up in the list.
3.20: This time, let's run in this race!
3.21: In the paddock, you can check the abilities and \nprediction rank of Umamusume running in the race!
3.22: First of all, let me explain the prediction marks. \nThe "◎", "○", "▲", and "△" marks indicate \nratings in that order, from highest to lowest.
3.23: The higher her ability and motivation, \nthe higher the expectations, and the more \nfavored an Umamusume is likely to be.
3.24: Of course, there is no guarantee of victory, but \nbroadly speaking the more favored she is, the better \nresults you can expect!
3.25: You can also change the strategy \nof your Umamusume in the paddock.
3.26: Of course choosing a strategy your \nUmamusume is strong at is a good idea.
3.27: We're all set now! \nIt's time to run the race!!
3.29: If you have any skill points left, please don't \nforget to use them.
3.30: Well then, that's it for training!
3.31: Once an Umamusume has been trained, she will be \nevaluated based on certain criteria and then \nregistered as a "Hall of Fame Umamusume".
3.32: Good luck in your quest for the highest rank!
3.33: Once training is complete, your Umamusume \nmay acquire a "factor".
3.34: When selecting an Umamusume as parent, her \ndesires and experiences will be passed on \nthrough their special bond as these "factors"!
3.35: Congratulations on finishing in first place!
3.36: Your Umamusume deserves lots of \npraise for her hard work!
3.37: After the race there is normally a winning live \nperformance, but since we're in the middle of \nyour introduction, let's skip that.
3.39: Although it was short in this introduction, the \nactual training period is 3 years.
3.40: Please cherish the days you spend \nwith any Umamusume in your care!
3.41: The three marks indicate the predictions of experts, \nand the expectations ranking shows the anticipation of fans.

49.29: 1st Anniv. Special\n1500 Jewels + SSR Exchange Ticket
49.65: 2nd Anniv. Special\n1500 Jewels + SSR Exchange Ticket
49.67: 2nd Anniv. Special\n5000 Jewels + SSR Exchange Ticket
49.81: 2.5th Anniv. Special\n5000 Jewels + SSR Exchange Ticket
49.83: 2.5th Anniv. Special\n1500 Jewels + SSR Exchange Ticket
49.87: New trainer support \n★3 pick ticket + 1500 jewels
49.88: New trainer support \nSSR pick ticket + 1500 jewels
49.90: TV Anime Season 3 Celebration \n★3 pick ticket + 1500 jewels

63.1:
A lot of things happen every day at the Tracen Academy. 
Choose a <color=#ff9900>nurturing scenario</color> and solve the problems 
surrounding the school. Conquering these scenarios 
will help your Umamusume grow!
63.2:
Spend 3 years with an Umamusume in the <color=#ff9900>Twinkle Series</color> 
and work together to make their <color=#ff9900>dreams come true</color> 
! The Umamusume' goals are diverse. Guide many 
different girls to become a great trainer.
63.3:
All of the Umamusume have unique personalities. Each Uma 
Musume has different basic abilities, skills, and aptitudes. 
You can train them as many times as you like, so let's start 
by <color=#ff9900>raising your favorite Umamusume</color>.
63.4:
Inheriting <color=#ff9900>feelings (factors)</color> increases ability and aptitude at 
the start of training, and your Umamusume will grow through 
<color=#ff9900>Inheritance Events</color>. Inherited girls won't disappear from the 
Hall of Fame, so take advantage to raise stronger Umamusume!
63.5: <color=#ff9900>Organize</color> support cards to receive corresponding <color=#ff9900>support effects</color> \nand <color=#ff9900>training events</color> from those characters. Note that you can \nnot use cards of the Umamusume you are training.
63.6: There are <color=#ff9900>types (specialty training)</color> of support cards. The \neffects they exhibit when training together are different.
63.7:
When you raise the bond gauge of your support card during 
training and perform your specialty training, <color=#ff9900>Friendship 
Training</color> will occur. In Friendship Training, your Umamusume 
will grow bigger than normal!
63.8:
Use <color=#ff9900>enhancement items</color> to increase your <color=#ff9900>Awakening Lv</color>. Raising 
your Awakening Lv will increase the number of skills you can 
acquire during training. Reinforcement items can be obtained 
through training and daily races.
63.9: Use <color=#ff9900>Umamusume pieces</color> to <color=#ff9900>uncap</color> them. This will increase the \nbasic ability of the Umamusume. Also, when they reach ★3 \nthey will receive a <color=#ff9900>victory outfit</color>.
63.10:
Use your <color=#ff9900>Support Pt</color> and <color=#ff9900>Money</color> to <color=#ff9900>increase the Lv</color>. As the Lv 
increases, your support effects will increase, giving you an 
edge in your training. Strengthening items can be obtained 
through training and daily races.
63.11: Use <color=#ff9900>copies of the same support card</color> to <color=#ff9900>uncap</color>. Uncapping \nincreases the upper level limit and you can further \nstrengthen the support card's Lvl.
63.12:
Support cards dupes can be converted into <color=#ff9900>Horseshoes</color> 
. These valuable items can be exchanged in the store. 
The first support card you acquire will be stored in 
the support card list, subsequent cards will be displayed 
in the vault and can be converted.
63.13:
When you complete training, your Umamusume will be saved in 
the <color=#ff9900>Hall of Fame</color>. Once there, she can enter the Team Stadium 
and various races, can be inherited from in training, or 
transferred, upon which she is irrevocably lost.
63.14:
Umamusume pieces can be converted into <color=#ff9900>clovers</color>. Clovers are 
valuable and can be exchanged for items in the store. Be 
careful when converting pieces, as they can be used to release 
the Umamusume you are training and to develop new talents.
63.16: Meeting new Umamusume and increasing their <color=#ff9900>affection</color> allows \nyou to progress through <color=#ff9900>their personal stories</color>. Rewards are \ngained for progressing through the stories.
63.17:
Form a <color=#ff9900>team</color> of Hall of Fame Umamusume and compete against 
teams from all over the country in the <color=#ff9900>Team Stadium</color>. Your team's 
<color=#ff9900>CLASS</color> will increase according to its success, and each week you 
will earn rewards according to the CLASS you belong to.
63.18: A <color=#ff9900>high score</color> will be recorded for outstanding race \nresults. Each week, the CLASS to which you belong \nwill change based on your high score.
63.19:
In the Team Stadium, five races with different <color=#ff9900>conditions</color> are 
held at a time. The higher your CLASS, the more people you can 
run in each race, up to a maximum of 15 Umamusume. Form the 
strongest team you can and challenge the Team Stadium!
63.20:
Form your own <color=#ff9900>team</color> of <color=#ff9900>Hall of Famers</color>. For each of 
the five races with different conditions, choose 
the Umamusume with the best aptitude. The <color=#ff9900>ace</color> horse 
girl will get <color=#ff9900>1.1 times</color> the score.
63.21: The more strong Umamusume you have in your team, the higher \nyour <color=#ff9900>team rating</color> will be and the higher your <color=#ff9900>team rank</color> will be. \nThe higher your team rank, the more rewards you can earn.
63.22:
In the Team Stadium, you will play against <color=#ff9900>opponents 
with similar team ratings</color>. The higher your team 
rating, the higher your score will be. Form a 
strong team and conquer the Team Stadium!
63.23:
Challenge the Legend Race with your saved Umamusume. The 
higher you finish, the more rewards you get. Tickets required 
for participation are replenished at 05:00 during the event 
period and when the LEGEND Umamusume is switched.
63.24: Take on the Daily Race with your Hall of Fame Umamusume. You \ncan earn various rewards depending on the races you challenge. \nEach day, you will receive up to the <color=#ff9900>maximum number of tickets</color>.
63.25:
In Practice, you can freely hold races under <color=#ff9900>any conditions 
you want</color>. In addition to the Hall of Fame Umamusume you have 
bred, you can also run races with <color=#ff9900>other trainers' Umamusume</color>. 
You can hold practice with up to 18 Umamusume at once!
63.26:
If you see any Umamusume you like in the Team Stadium 
or room match, you can register her as your <color=#ff9900>Training 
Partner</color> so that you can run races with her. The representative 
Umamusume of the friends you are following will also 
be able to run in the race.
63.27: You can <color=#ff9900>share</color> your favorite <color=#ff9900>Hall of Fame Umamusume</color> with your \ncircle and SNS. Actively register your Practice Partners from \ncircle members and friends to enhance your practice!
63.30: Join a <color=#ff9900>circle</color> with other trainers from around \nthe country. You can interact with other members \nand help each other with training.
63.31: Members can give each other a <color=#ff9900>variety of items</color>\n. You can also rent each other's <color=#ff9900>representative \nUmamusume</color> for inheritance at a discount.
63.32:
<size=26>You can watch live performances of <color=#ff9900>songs</color> you have acquired. 
Choose main and back dancers from obtained Umamusume 
and acquired costumes to watch the live with your favorite 
combination. Songs marked with <color=#ff9900>"Singing"</color>, are voiced 
by the selected Umamusume. Songs can be acquired through 
the main story and training.</size>
63.33:
You can check and set your trainer information. On your 
<color=#ff9900>birthday</color>, you will receive a congratulatory comment from Uma 
Musume on the home screen, and changing your <color=#ff9900>gender</color> will change 
some scenarios. (Gender can be changed at any time)
63.34:
You can set up a <color=#ff9900>representative Umamusume</color> and <color=#ff9900>support card</color> to 
help your followers in their training. You will earn <color=#ff9900>Friend Pt 
the next day</color> depending on the number of times you do this. 
(This will be given as a gift)
63.35: You can earn titles through <color=#ff9900>title missions</color> and <color=#ff9900>events</color>. You can \nchange the title you have earned at any time.
63.36:
Help the Chairman reach her dream! You can earn <color=#ff9900>trophies and 
rewards</color> when you win graded races during training, or Legend 
Races. In addition, you can earn rewards by completing 
missions to collect the specified number of trophies.
63.37:
You can select the representative Umamusume and support 
card of the friends you <color=#ff9900>follow</color> from each list in training. 
You also earn more Friend Pt by helping a <color=#ff9900>mutual follower</color> 
to train. If you don't have many followers, try looking 
in the <color=#ff9900>recommendations</color>.
63.38:
Collect records related to Umamusume to raise your <color=#ff9900>Index Lv</color>. 
You'll accumulate Index Exp based on the evaluation points 
you've earned through training and the stories you've viewed, 
and you'll earn rewards as your Index Lv increases.
63.39: Take aim and catch Umamusume plushies (Paka-Puchi)! \nYou have <color=#ff9900>3 attempts</color> to catch at least one. \nYour Umamusume might  even gain a <color=#ff9900>new hint</color>!?
63.40:
Congratulations on your <color=#ff9900>CLASS 2</color> promotion! The <color=#ff9900>second slot</color> for 
team formation has been released. The second slot for team 
formation has been released, allowing you to organize more Uma 
Musume for the Hall of Fame.
63.41: Congratulations on your <color=#ff9900>CLASS 3</color> promotion! The <color=#ff9900>third \nslot</color> for team formation has been released, allowing \nyou to organize more Hall of Fame Umamusume.
63.42:
The aim of the training is to achieve good results 
in the <color=#ff9900>target races</color> set for each Umamusume. In order 
to achieve good results in races, you need to <color=#ff9900>develop 
your basic abilities</color> through <color=#ff9900>training</color>!
63.43:
By acquiring <color=#ff9900>skills</color>, you can gain a <color=#ff9900>variety of 
effects</color> in <color=#ff9900>races</color>. The Skill Points needed to acquire 
skills are mainly obtained through races, but can 
also be obtained through some events.
63.44:
If your Umamusume's <color=#ff9900>energy or motivation is low</color> she will not 
be able to perform at her best in training or races. <color=#ff9900>Resting</color> 
restores energy, and <color=#ff9900>going out</color> boosts motivation. Always pay 
attention to her condition!
63.45:
During training, you may acquire <color=#ff9900>conditions</color> that have a 
negative effect on your Umamusume's training and physical 
condition. The <color=#ff9900>Infirmary</color> can eliminate such conditions, 
so think about making use of it quickly.
63.46: You can execute various commands while training your Uma \nMusume! Use each command in a well-balanced manner to make \nyour Umamusume into a great Umamusume!
63.47:
<size=26>From the latter half of June in Junior class, you can start 
<color=#ff9900>racing</color>. Train your Umamusume well and aim for <color=#ff9900>first place</color>! In 
races, you earn <color=#ff9900>Skill Points</color> to acquire skills and <color=#ff9900>Fans</color> to run 
in big races, based on your finishing position. You'll also 
earn random items based on your position and margin.</size>
63.48:
Umamusume make their first appearance on the racing stage in 
their <color=#ff9900>make debut</color>. If they finish first, they can run in 
various races. If they don't, you'll have to try to win one of 
the <color=#ff9900>Maiden Races</color> available!
63.49:
<color=#ff9900>Basic abilities</color> such as speed and stamina, 
gained through training, are linked to <color=#ff9900>the various 
abilities displayed during races</color>. Which you need varies 
greatly with <color=#ff9900>distance</color> and <color=#ff9900>running strategy</color>, so <color=#ff9900>create 
a training menu that suits her</color>!
63.50:
The <color=#ff9900>surface and distance</color> where the races take place differ. 
Your Umamusume suits different tracks depending on her 
<color=#ff9900>surface and distance aptitudes</color>. Aim for races that are <color=#ff9900>marked 
with a ★</color> in the list, and go for the win!
63.51: The races are divided into five grades: <color=#ff9900>Pre-Open, Open, GIII, \nGII, and GI</color>. Let's start with the <color=#ff9900>Pre-Open, Open</color> to win the \nhighest G1 race in the Twinkle Series!
63.52:
You can grow your Umamusume's <color=#ff9900>basic abilities</color> by 
spending <color=#ff9900>energy</color> to <color=#ff9900>train</color> her. In addition to <color=#ff9900>recovering</color> 
energy, more <color=#ff9900>Skill Points</color> can be gained from the 
Wisdom training than other training.
63.53:
Training with Umamusume organized as a <color=#ff9900>support card</color> will 
increase your <color=#ff9900>training efficiency and bond gauge</color>. When the 
bond gauge is full, <color=#ff9900>Friendship Training</color> can occur. You may <color=#ff9900>gain 
various benefits</color> if certain others watch you train as well.
63.54:
When a support card Umamusume has a <color=#ff9900>! mark</color> on her, grab your 
chance to <color=#ff9900>increase Hint Lv of one of this partner's skills</color> upon 
successfully completing the training session. This will confer 
a <color=#ff9900>discount on the Skill Pt needed to acquire the skill</color>.
63.55:
If you train your Umamusume when her <color=#ff9900>energy is low</color>, she may 
<color=#ff9900>fail the training</color> and her ability may not improve. There are 
<color=#ff9900>various disadvantages</color> to failing a training session, so always 
keep an eye on her <color=#ff9900>energy and failure rate</color>!
63.56:
By spending <color=#ff9900>Skill Points</color>, you can acquire <color=#ff9900>skills</color> that activate 
during races. There are various conditions to activate skills, 
such as the <color=#ff9900>race distance and running strategy</color>, so try to 
<color=#ff9900>acquire skills that match her aptitudes</color>.
63.57:
The <color=#ff9900>hint Lv</color> of a skill may be increased by the result 
of a <color=#ff9900>Support Card or Umamusume Event</color>. The skill Pt 
you <color=#ff9900>consume will be discounted</color> depending on the hint 
Lv, so organize support cards that have the skills 
you want to acquire to get the best deals.
63.58:
<size=26>There are three main types of skills. <color=#ff9900>Unique skills</color> are special 
skills that your Umamusume starts with. <color=#ff9900>Rare skills</color> are 
powerful skills found in special situations. <color=#ff9900>Normal Skills</color> are 
skills found in various situations. There are also skills that 
can only be acquired by <color=#ff9900>inheriting certain factors</color>.</size>
63.59:
If you raise the level of your support card to a 
certain level, you will get a <color=#ff9900>support bonus 
that will increase your score in the Team Stadium</color>. 
Let's raise the lvl of many support cards!
63.62: During the event period, <color=#ff9900>train your Umamusume</color> and earn <color=#ff9900>Event \nPoints</color>. By collecting Event Points, you can earn various <color=#ff9900>rewards</color>.
63.63:
Collecting Event Points will allow you to advance through the 
<color=#ff9900>event-only story</color>. By advancing the story and clearing event 
missions, you can earn <color=#ff9900>event limited support cards, rainbow 
fragments, and titles</color>.
63.64: At the end of training, any <color=#ff9900>event bonus Umamusume or support \ncards</color> will confer a <color=#ff9900>bonus to the event points gained</color>.
63.65: You can get <color=#ff9900>Event Pt and Roulette Coins</color> by \ncompleting event missions. You can also earn \nRoulette Coins from the <color=#ff9900>daily missions</color>.
63.66: You can play <color=#ff9900>roulette derby</color> using <color=#ff9900>roulette coins</color> \nIf you <color=#ff9900>achieve bingo</color>, you can get <color=#ff9900>event limited \nsupport cards and gold fragments</color>.
63.67: During the event period, you can earn <color=#ff9900>roulette coins</color> by \n<color=#ff9900>training Umamusume</color> and completing <color=#ff9900>event missions</color>. Collect \n<color=#ff9900>roulette coins</color>to spin the <color=#ff9900>roulette derby</color> wheel.
63.68: You can get <color=#ff9900>roulette rewards</color> according to your finishing order \nin the roulette derby. When you get a roulette reward you've \nnever gotten before, it's your chance to BINGO!
63.69:
Cells will be filled according to roulette rewards earned. 
When 3 consecutive squares are filled (on any axis), <color=#ff9900>a line is 
completed</color>, and you will receive a <color=#ff9900>BINGO reward</color> based on number 
of lines. Complete <color=#ff9900>8 lines of BINGO</color>to exchange your first 3 sheets.
63.70:
Run in the <color=#ff9900>Aoharu Hai</color>, held the turn after June and December 
end, and aim for victory with your team. Winning will increase 
your <color=#ff9900>team ranking</color>, and your <color=#ff9900>Umamusume and team members will 
grow</color>. Train a strong Umamusume to <color=#ff9900>win lots of Aoharu Hai</color>!
63.71:
Put together a team to win the Aoharu Hai! With races in each 
category, the winner will be the one with <color=#ff9900>more wins</color> out of 
five. <color=#ff9900>Winning raises your team ranking</color>, more so the higher 
your opponent's ranking.
63.72: By using the pieces you have collected, you can <color=#ff9900>release</color> \nyour breeding Umamusume. Once released, you will \nbe able to take charge of them in training.
63.73: Register 3 Umamusume to <color=#ff9900>match</color> and battle with <color=#ff9900>other trainers</color> \nin real time! Raise strong Umamusume and aim for glory!
63.74:
There are two leagues, the <color=#ff9900>Open League</color> and the <color=#ff9900>Grade 
League</color>, and you can choose the one that suits you 
best Depending on the league, the upper limit of the 
<color=#ff9900>breeding rank</color> of the Hall of Fame Umamusume you can 
register to run in the race will differ.
63.75:
<color=#ff9900>Room Match</color> allows you to race against other trainers 
with your Hall of Fame Umamusume <color=#ff9900>Host</color>: Set your own 
conditions for the race <color=#ff9900>Join</color>: Join another trainer's 
race. <color=#ff9900>Watch</color>: Enter an ID to watch the race.
63.76:
The race held will be GI. There are two modes. <color=#ff9900>Simple Mode</color> 
allows you to hold a race right away. <color=#ff9900>Detailed mode</color> allows you 
to choose weather, participation conditions, etc. first. Up to 
<color=#ff9900>3 Umamusume per person</color> can be entered.
63.77:
<color=#ff9900>The league is made up of three rounds</color>. Starting from Round 2, 
you will be divided into Group A and Group B, and the places 
you advance to will depend on your performance in each round 
and group. Let's move on to the final round and win the <color=#ff9900>winner</color>!
63.78:
Recruit participants for your races from the participation 
list. Trainers close to you can also be recruited using 
the <color=#ff9900>Circle and SNS Sharing functions</color>. For future reference, 
<color=#ff9900>you can save your favorite races</color>. Have a go organizing 
a race with your friends!
63.80:
In Special Transfers, you can <color=#ff9901>transfer your trained Umamusume 
to another trainer's team for rewards</color>. Be aware that once 
you transfer someone, she will be gone and you will not be 
able to get her back.
63.81: Each team has its own expectations. These not only come with \n<color=#ff9901>different rewards</color>, but <color=#ff9901>the higher the expectations, the more \nluxurious the rewards</color> for transferring your Umamusume to them.
63.82: Teams with high expectations will reward a piece of the \ntransferred <color=#ff9901>Hall of Fame Umamusume</color> as a thank you gift.
63.83:
If you train at a training location where a team member has a 
special icon, "<color=#ff9900>Aoharu Special Training</color>" will occur, and <color=#ff9900>that 
team member's basic abilities will increase</color>. Let's use the 
Aoharu Training to grow our team so we can win the Aoharu Hai!
63.84:
Furthermore, a Special Training session <color=#ff9900>with 2 or more</color> 
team members, will <color=#ff9900>boost your Umamusume's training 
efficiency</color> as well. <color=#ff9900>Basic abilities and skill points 
gained</color> will also increase <color=#ff9900>the more team members</color> participate.
63.86:
Team members you have had many Special Trainings with 
can have an <color=#ff9900>Aoharu Spirit Explosion</color> once. Their <color=#ff9900>basic 
abilities will increase greatly</color> and <color=#ff9900>your Umamusume will 
also grow and get Skill Hints</color> The key to success is <color=#ff9900>generating 
many Aoharu Spirit Explosions</color>!
63.87: You can check the items you currently have. You can also use \nconsumable items. Some items can be converted to Money. \n<color=#ff9900>Converting items cannot be undone</color>, so be careful.
63.88:
As team members grow, <color=#ff9900>team strength</color> will increase and you will 
receive gifts from Tazuna. Also, each member's <color=#ff9900>Training Lv 
will increase</color> with their basic ability. <color=#ff9900>The strength of your 
team will lead to the growth of your Umamusume</color> , so be 
proactive in training your team!
63.89:
The <color=#ff9900>team title</color> is an <color=#ff9900>evaluation of your overall</color> team strength 
and team ranking. <color=#ff9900>The better the team title you have, the more 
your Umamusume will grow in the ending</color> Let's win Aoharu Hai 
and get the strongest team title!
63.90: Using <color=#ff9900>Event Boost</color> you can spend twice the TP \nat the start of training to gain double the \n<color=#ff9900>Event Pt</color> and <color=#ff9900>Roulette coins</color> at the end.
63.91: You can <color=#ff9900>uncap</color> support cards by using <color=#ff9900>duplicates of the same card</color> \n. The level limit will be increased. SR and SSR support cards \ncan also be uncapped by using <color=#ff9900>Release Crystals</color>.
63.92:
When you end training in <color=#ff9900>Showtime Mode</color>, your <color=#ff9900>SHOW Gauge</color> will 
rise according to your progress and the difficulty level. You 
will receive <color=#ff9900>additional rewards</color> according to the number of 
times you've filled your SHOW Gauge to MAX.
63.93:
In Showtime Mode, the <color=#ff9900>opponent Umamusume</color> will become stronger 
in training races. When you see the <color=#ff9900>good ending of your Umamusume 
</color> at the chosen difficulty level, the next level will be 
unlocked and can be challenged from next training.
63.94: You can earn more points by training Umamusume \n<color=#ff9900>according to their aptitude</color> and by achieving \nthe specified <color=#ff9900>Score Bonus</color> conditions.
63.95: In the <color=#ff9900>Trainer Proficiency Exam</color>, you can check the <color=#ff9900>usage rate \nof support cards</color> for each test in the ranking!
63.96:
A scenario without individual goals, <color=#ff9900>instead chasing "Result 
Points"</color>. Acquire fixed amounts from each of the 3 years! You 
can freely enter any races during training, and obtained Pts 
depend on the race's grade and finishing position!
63.97: <color=#ff9900>Once all training objectives are complete</color>, you can challenge \nthe <color=#ff9900>Twinkle Star Climax</color>! Emerge victorious over the 3-race \nbattle to claim your place as "Twinkle Top Star"!
63.98:
When entering races, you will <color=#ff9900>obtain Shop Coins</color>! Shop 
Coins can be traded for training items in the special 
shop. Training items can increase stats, recover energy, 
boost training growths, and have <color=#ff9900>various other effects 
that are sure to help your training</color>!
63.99:
<color=#ff9900>After each second half of December</color>, when changing years, <color=#ff9900>the 
most outstanding Umamusume is recognized</color>. Do well in races 
while deepening bonds with your supporters to increase your 
fans! When chosen, your Umamusume's unique skill will level 
up, in addition to other improvements!
63.100:
Sometimes Rivals will enter races. When <color=#ff9900>entering and winning 
those races</color> your <color=#ff9900>Umamusume's stats will grow</color>, and she can 
<color=#ff9900>obtain Skill Hints</color>. Grow your Umamusume more by having them 
fight these tough opponents!
63.101:
In the Twinkle Star Climax, <color=#ff9900>you gain Result Pt based 
on your finishing position</color>, and the <color=#ff9900>Umamusume with 
the most Pts over 3 races is the winner</color>. Aim for the 
top with your carefully trained Umamusume!
63.102:
In Practice, you can freely hold races under <color=#ff9900>any conditions 
you want</color>. In addition to the Hall of Fame Umamusume you have 
bred, you can also run races with <color=#ff9900>other trainers' Umamusume</color>. 
You can hold practice with up to 18 Umamusume at once!
63.103:
If you see any Umamusume you like in the Team Stadium 
or room match, you can register her as your <color=#ff9900>Training 
Partner</color> so that you can run races with her. The representative 
Umamusume of the friends you are following will also 
be able to run in the race.
63.104: You can <color=#ff9900>share</color> your favorite <color=#ff9900>Hall of Fame Umamusume</color> with your \ncircle and SNS. Actively register your Practice Partners from \ncircle members and friends to enhance your practice!
63.105:
Save Umas in <color=#ff9900>My Entrants</color> to <color=#ff9900>select them easily</color> during 
registration! You can also save them from the results screen. 
Removing Training Partners, will remove them from My Entrants 
as well, so be careful!
63.106:
Save Umas in <color=#ff9900>My Entrants</color> to <color=#ff9900>select them easily</color> during 
registration! You can also save them from the results screen. 
Removing Training Partners, will remove them from My Entrants 
as well, so be careful!
63.107: You can view the <color=#ff9900>Top 100 highest scorers</color> in the \nranking! The <color=#ff9900>Top 30 Umamusume</color> can be <color=#ff9900>rented \nwithout limit</color> in the relevant scenario.
63.108: <color=#ff9900>Trial Coins</color> are earned for exams, and extra can be earned \nthrough <color=#ff9900>Score Bonuses</color>, <color=#ff9900>Exam Grades</color>, and <color=#ff9900>Missions</color>.
63.109: You can increase the <color=#ff9900>Hint Lv</color> of your Umamusume's skills by \nusing <color=#ff9900>upgrade items</color>. When doing so, she will start training \nwith her <color=#ff9900>Hint Lv already raised</color> for those skills.
63.110: Race in the Carnival to gain <color=#ff9900>Carnival Pts</color>. Points are awarded \nfor skill uses and finishing position.
63.111: As you complete <color=#ff9900>Carnival Races</color>, your <color=#ff9900>Challenge Gauge</color> will fill. \nWhen full, you can enter a <color=#ff9900>Challenge Race</color>. Challenge Races \ncome in <color=#ff9900>VERY HARD and EXTREME</color> difficulties.
63.112:
Your Umamusume will gain the <color=#ff9900>Carnival Factor</color> when 
finishing top 5 in an event race. When an Umamusume 
inherits this factor, she will gain <color=#ff9900>bonus stats and 
a chance to max mood</color> in the event races.
63.113: When an Umamusume with the <color=#ff9900>Carnival Bonus Skill</color> finishes top 5 \nin an event race, the factor will <color=#ff9900>Lv up</color>. The <color=#ff9900>stat bonus and \nmax mood chance will increase</color> with skill level.
63.114: The <color=#ff9900>Carnival pts</color> obtained in Racing Carnival \nraces can be <color=#ff9900>traded for items</color> in the shop!
63.115: Challenge the daily Legend races! Pieces of \nthe challenged Legend Umamusume can be acquired. \nTickets will <color=#ff9900>refill to max</color> every day.
63.116: Create your own <color=#ff9900>Trainer Card</color>, and share it as an image on \nsocial media. Show your info along with Umamusume, support and \n<color=#ff9900>customizable graphics</color>.
63.117: <color=#ff9900>Factors</color> for your representative Umamusume can also be <color=#ff9900>shared on \nsocial media</color>. Show off your glorious Umamusume on your card!
63.118: The <color=#ff9900>Snapshot function</color> allows you to take photos of <color=#ff9900>Races, \nLives, and Stories</color>. Snapshots can be processed and \nedited in a few ways to add your own flair.
63.119: Saved snapshots are stored in the <color=#ff9900>Photo Library</color> and accessible at \nany time、They can also be used on your <color=#ff9900>Trainer or Circle Cards</color>.
63.120:
When entering races, you will <color=#ff9900>obtain Shop Coins</color>! Shop 
Coins can be traded for training items in the special 
shop. Training items can increase stats, recover energy, 
boost training growths, and have <color=#ff9900>various other effects 
that are sure to help your training</color>!
63.121:
For your first training <color=#ff9900>we recommend you play the URA Finals 
scenario</color> to get to know the Umamusume better! Many things 
happen on the path you both take towards her unique goals. 
Aim to win on the big, dream-like stage of the URA Finals!
63.122: Each scenario <color=#ff9900>has many exclusive events!</color> We hope you will enjoy \ndiscovering new aspects of the Umamusume through their daily \nlife and their expressions as they go through the seasons!
63.123: <color=#ff9900>Everyone's Top Umadol Project</color> is an event where rewards are \ngained for obtaining fans through training. Personal rewards \nare obtained based on total fans gained in training mode.
63.124: When finishing training in <color=#ff9900>Golshi-chan Mode</color> you \nwill gain rewards based on progress. In Golshi-chan \nmode <color=#ff9900>opponents in races</color> will be stronger.
63.125: Overall rewards are based on <color=#ff9900>total fans gained by all trainers \nin the event</color>. The more fans, the more luxurious the rewards.
63.126:
<color=#ff9900>Room Match</color> allows you to race against other trainers 
with your Hall of Fame Umamusume <color=#ff9900>Host</color>: Set your own 
conditions for the race <color=#ff9900>Join</color>: Join another trainer's 
race. <color=#ff9900>Watch</color>: Enter an ID to watch the race.
63.127:
The race held will be GI. There are two modes. <color=#ff9900>Simple Mode</color> 
allows you to hold a race right away. <color=#ff9900>Detailed mode</color> allows you 
to choose weather, participation conditions, etc. first. Up to 
<color=#ff9900>3 Umamusume per person</color> can be entered.
63.128:
Recruit participants for your races from the participation 
list. Trainers close to you can also be recruited using 
the <color=#ff9900>Circle and SNS Sharing functions</color>. For future reference, 
<color=#ff9900>you can save your favorite races</color>. Have a go organizing 
a race with your friends!
63.129: Save Umamusume in <color=#ff9900>My Entrants</color> to <color=#ff9900>select them easily</color> during \nregistration! You can also save them from the results screen.
63.130: Save Umamusume in <color=#ff9900>My Entrants</color> to <color=#ff9900>select them easily</color> during \nregistration! You can also save them from the results screen.
63.131:
Dress your Umamusume in your favorite outfits! 
Changing the outfit of an Umamusume will change it 
for <color=#ff9900>all of her Hall of Fame versions</color>. Note that 
in some situations the outfit won't display.
63.132: You can select <color=#ff9900>Double TP Usage</color> at the start of training to \n<color=#ff9900>double SHOW gauge fill rate</color> at the end.
63.133: After 4 Promotional Lives, the <color=#ff9900>Grand Live</color> is held! \nKeeping things fresh and <color=#ff9900>learning various tracks</color> \nfor each Live will greatly benefit your Umamusume!
63.134: Through training, <color=#ff9900>5 different Performances</color> can be earned! \nWhich ones go with which training changes every turn.
63.135: The Performances earned increase with the \n<color=#ff9900>training's level</color> and the <color=#ff9900>amount of Umamusume participating</color>. \nFriendship training will also provide 2 Performances!
63.136: The Performances earned can be spend on <color=#ff9900>Lessons</color> to \ngain <color=#ff9900>Tracks or Live Techniques</color>. Both of these are \nhighly useful to the <color=#ff9900>development of your Umamusume</color>.
63.137:
Performances can be spent on <color=#ff9900>Lessons</color> to gain <color=#ff9900>Tracks or 
Live Techniques</color>! Learning these will provide an immediate 
<color=#ff9900>Talent Bonus</color>, and Tracks will additionally provide 
a <color=#ff9900>Live Bonus</color> which will be active from the next Live 
until the end of training.
63.138: When lacking the Performances for a Lesson, it can be \n<color=#ff9900>reserved</color>. Doing so will display the <color=#ff9900>Performances needed</color> \nto learn it in the Training screens.
63.139:
Each Track learned will increase the <color=#ff9900>Live Anticipation</color>. 
Maxing this gauge will ensure the live's <color=#ff9900>Great Success</color>. 
Anticipation will reset every live, so prepare new Tracks 
for each live!
63.140:
At a <color=#ff9900>Live</color>, the <color=#ff9900>songs learnt will be played</color>. With a specific 
number of new Tracks, the <color=#ff9900>live will be a Great Success</color>. 
Umamusume will <color=#ff9900>grow more</color> when the live is a Great Sucess, 
so aim for this using the Anticipation gauge as reference.
63.141: When new Tracks are played at a Live, their \n<color=#ff9900>Live Bonus</color> will be active from the next turn. \nSimilar bonuses will <color=#ff9900>stack</color>.
63.142:
In <color=#ff9901>Special Transfer StarHorse4 Edition</color> 
you can transfer your trained Umamusume to another team 
to receive rewards. Be careful, the transfer is permanent, 
and you can't just call those girls back!
63.143: The <color=#ff9901>expectations</color> of the receiving teams differ, and based on \nthat and the Umamusume you sent the rewards can change. \n<color=#ff9901>That one trainer</color> seems to have a request of <color=#ff9901>☆4 difficulty</color>!
63.144: In ☆3 difficulty requests, you will receive <color=#ff9901>pieces of the \nUmamusume you sent</color>. Moreover, from this difficulty onwards \nyou can get <color=#ff9901>Star Fruits</color> exclusive to this <color=#ff9901>StarHorse4 Edition</color>.
63.145:
Take on Scout Races with a team of 7. The Team captain 
will be one of your trained Umamusume. The others can be 
selected through <color=#ff9900>scouting</color>. Build the strongest team through 
continuous <color=#ff9900>racing and scouting</color>!
63.146:
You can obtain up to 5 <color=#ff9900>Scout Race Tickets</color> every day at 12. 
Daily missions and items can also grant you some. 
<color=#ff9900>Every 3 races</color>, the <color=#ff9900>race details</color> will change. You can check 
this from the Race Schedule.
63.147: Entering Scout Races will grant <color=#ff9900>Scout Pt</color>. The amount \nwill vary based on race result, opponent team rank, and \nany bonuses. Aim to win a variety of different races!
63.148: During <color=#ff9900>Scout Time</color>, you can <color=#ff9900>scout</color> the opponent's Umamusume \nand swap around your own team. The <color=#ff9900>Scout Pt</color> needed \nto scout depend on the target Umamusume's rank.
63.149: Strengthen your team and <color=#ff9900>increase team rank</color> to \nreceive rewards. In addition, clear <color=#ff9900>limited missions</color> \nto gain more rewards!
63.150:
When you <color=#ff9900>win</color> a <color=#ff9900>Scout Race</color>, the team captain and members 
are registered in the <color=#ff9900>Roster</color>, and you will get a bonus to 
the entire team's stats and your Scout Pt. Further, by 
drafting specific combinations of Umamusume in your team 
you can obtain <color=#ff9900>Team Skills</color> upon victory.
63.151: The <color=#ff9900>Event Boost</color> lets you use double the TP \nat the start of training to double the amount of <color=#ff9900>Trial Coin</color> received at the end.
63.152:
You can fill the <color=#ff9900>Stroll Gauge</color> by playing <color=#ff9900>various parts of 
the game</color> or through the <color=#ff9900>stroll login bonus</color>. Once the gauge 
is at <color=#ff9900>MAX</color>, you can <color=#ff9900>take a stroll</color> with one of your Umamusume. 
 
※The gauge will fill from play after using your login bonus.
63.153: With the Photo Studio you can take <color=#ff9900>photos \nat training, outings</color>, and various other settings.
63.154: After selecting an Umamusume to photograph, you can set up \nthe <color=#ff9900>seasons, locations, and so on</color>. For <color=#ff9900>training photos</color> \npartners can also be selected.
63.155: During shooting the action can be <color=#ff9900>paused or looped</color>. \nFind the perfect timing to snap your favourite shots! \nPhotos can also be <color=#ff9900>edited with filters and the like</color>.
63.156:
Going for a stroll increases your <color=#ff9900>Stroll Partner's Friendship</color>. 
Different <color=#ff9900>destinations</color> will play unique animations and 
provide different <color=#ff9900>rewards</color>. During the campaign you can 
rewatch any animations you've seen by long-clicking 
an Umamusume.
63.157:
On the KIRARI MAGIC SHOW campaign page you can check 
not only campaign info but from 21 December you can join 
in on the TOKYO MEGA ILLUMI collab event, as well as 
find a gift hiding in the <color=#ff9900>present box once a day</color>.
63.158:
The Umamusume gather at the Ooi Racecourse for the 
TOKYO MEGA ILLUMI Christmas Live collab. But the 
MEGA TREE's decorations are lagging behind!? It's time 
for the Umamusume's power to shine☆ With everyone's help 
the MEGA TREE will be glittering in no time!
63.159: <color=#ff9900>Happy Meek</color> will appear in training! \nWork together with her and aim to enter the URA Finals!
63.160: Training with her can trigger a <color=#ff9900>Duel</color> around a specific stat \nor energy level! The higher this chosen Duel Subject is, \nthe easier it will be to win the Duel, so train well!
63.161: Should you manage to win a certain number of Duels, \na <color=#ff9900>stronger Happy Meek</color> will appear in the URA Finals! \nTrain your Umamusume to take victory on the Finals stage!
63.162:
After a team member has had a Spirit Explosion, they can have 
one further <color=#ff9900>EX Spirit Explosion</color>! This will <color=#ff9900>grant them even more 
stats, as will your Umamusume, who will additionally receive a special 
skill hint</color>! EX Spirit Explosions add even more fire to your training!
63.163: Under <color=#ff9900>certain conditions</color>, you can face a <color=#ff9900>Powerhouse Team</color> in \nthe Aoharu Hai! When winning against this team your Umamusume \nwill grow considerably! <color=#ff9900>Something may happen in the finals</color> too…!?
63.164:
In the TOKYO MEGA ILLUMI collab event, KIRARI MAGIC 
SHOW, you will receive rewards for gathering <color=#ff9900>ornaments 
for the tree</color> from training and missions. Individual rewards 
will be handed out based on the amount you collect.
63.165:
With the <color=#ff9900>ornaments gathered by all trainers</color> we can make 
the MEGA TREE glitter as it should. Watch the <color=#ff9900>tree change</color> 
on the event homepage and help claim the extravagant 
global event rewards by collecting tons of ornaments!
63.166:
Reach for your Umamusume's dreams over 3 years 
with the aid of the three goddesses! 
<color=#ff9900>Clear all goals to enter the special Grand Masters race!</color> 
Hold your own against the goddesses and aim for victory!
63.167:
The goddesses will bestow <color=#ff9900>Knowledge Shards</color> upon you 
when training, resting, going out, or racing! These shards 
will grant <color=#ff9900>increased stat gains</color> and other useful effects. 
<color=#ff9900>And friendship training grants 2 shards at once!?</color>
63.168: Every 2 <color=#ff9900>Knowledge Shards</color> will also grant a <color=#ff9900>Knowledge Crystal</color>! \nThese also bestow effects to improve your training. <color=#ff9900>Crystals inherit \neffects from their shards</color>, so pile them up and strengthen your Umamusume!
63.169:
Shards and Crystals collected show in the Knowledge Tree. 
Reach the end to obtain <color=#ff9900>Goddess's Wisdom</color>! Use this wisdom 
whenever you wish to <color=#ff9900>power up various actions for 1 turn</color>! 
The effects vary per goddess, so check the details in the tree.
63.170: Before you can enter the Grand Masters, you will face a \n<color=#ff9900>special race at the end of each year</color>! Seize victory in all of \nthem with your Umamusume and the power of the goddesses!
63.171:
The Grand Masters is 1 special race, facing the ultimate rivals in 
the <color=#ff9900>three goddesses</color> themselves! <color=#ff9900>Darley Arabian, Godolphin Barb, 
and Byerley Turk</color> await! Challenge them with your well-trained 
Umamusume and seize victory!
63.172:
This event is divided in a <color=#ff9901>Main Stage</color> and an <color=#ff9901>Extra Stage</color>. 
In the Main Stage you take on races with a team of three. 
Based on how you do, your <color=#ff9901>League Score</color> will increase, 
and based on this score, your <color=#ff9901>League Rank</color> increases, 
granting various rewards!
63.176: Fill the research gauge by <color=#ff9900>playing various content</color>. \nWhen the gauge is filled at least once, return to the event page \nto receive an amount of <color=#ff9900>research rewards</color> equal to gauge fills.
63.177:
<color=#ff9900>The login bloom bonus</color>, <color=#ff9900>completing training</color>, and <color=#ff9900>entering stadium </color> 
will fill your <color=#ff9900>bloom gauge</color>. When the gauge is at <color=#ff9900>MAX</color> you can 
<color=#ff9900>move 1 cell further</color> on the main event page. 
 
※ The gauge will fill from play after using your bloom bonus.
63.178:
Upon moving cells, their <color=#ff9900>local episodes</color> are unlocked, and their 
<color=#ff9900>reward</color> acquired. On 4/2 & 4/3 at 12:00 a <color=#ff9900>new area</color> will unlock, 
allowing you to move into new cells. 
 
※ The bloom gauge won't fill if there are no new cells to move to.
63.179:
During training, fulfilling the conditions for the Rare Skills 
unlocked by awakening an Umamusume allows you to upgrade 
them to powerful <color=#ff9900>Evolved Skills</color> unique to each Umamusume 
at the end of training.
63.180:
By spending <color=#ff9900>Skill Points</color>, you can acquire <color=#ff9900>skills</color> that activate 
during races. There are various conditions to activate skills, 
such as the <color=#ff9900>race distance and running strategy</color>, so try to 
<color=#ff9900>acquire skills that match her aptitudes</color>.
63.181:
The <color=#ff9900>hint Lv</color> of a skill may be increased by the result 
of a <color=#ff9900>Support Card or Umamusume Event</color>. The skill Pt 
you <color=#ff9900>consume will be discounted</color> depending on the hint 
Lv, so organize support cards that have the skills 
you want to acquire to get the best deals.
63.182:
<size=26>There are three main types of skills. <color=#ff9900>Unique skills</color> are special 
skills that your Umamusume starts with. <color=#ff9900>Rare skills</color> are 
powerful skills found in special situations. <color=#ff9900>Normal Skills</color> are 
skills found in various situations. There are also skills that 
can only be acquired by <color=#ff9900>inheriting certain factors</color>.</size>
63.184:
The <color=#ff9900>Factor Research Reports</color> obtained as rewards for research 
allow you to increase the <color=#ff9900>★</color> of an Umamusume's <color=#ff9900>factor</color>. 
※ Reports apply to most but not all factors. 
※ Reports don't carry over to next event.
63.185: Using the <color=#ff9900>Event Boost</color>, twice the TP will be used at the \nstart of training to double the <color=#ff9900>Research Gauge's fill rate</color>.
63.186: Each area's final cell is the <color=#ff9900>destination</color>. \nReaching it unlocks a <color=#ff9900>special video</color>. \nVideos are available from 4/1～4/3 at 19:00 and 4/4 at 12:00.
63.187: For a time you can <color=#ff9900>cheer for an Umamusume by hitting \nthe "Neighce!" button</color>! Doing so grants you some \n<color=#ff9900>neighce rewards</color> and can be done once per block (A-B).
63.188: The Extra Stage has opened! You can watch the main race \nfor the A and B blocks and each race of your own team. \nWatching races grants rewards too!
63.189: Circles can create their own original <color=#ff9901>Circle Cards</color> and share \nthem as images on <color=#ff9901>social media</color>. These are customizable cards \nshowing the circle's details and other info.
63.190:
At <color=#ff9900>12am every day</color> you receive <color=#ff9900>5 League Tickets</color>, each of 
which grants entry to <color=#ff9900>5 races</color>. Each race features 5 teams, 
with the weather and going randomized every race. 
No other race conditions will change.
63.191:
With each entered race, your <color=#ff9900>Hero Gauge</color> will fill, 
and when MAXed you gain access to a <color=#ff9900>Hero Skill</color> 
for <color=#ff9900>5 races</color>! Some Hero Skills can be activated 
by using Race Items.
63.192:
From <color=#ff9900>BRONZE1 to PLATINUM4</color>, there are 16 League Ranks. 
Reaching PLATINUM1 bestows a <color=#ff9900>unique title</color> featuring the 
name of one of your entered Umamusume. Which one can be 
freely chosen from those who meet the requirements. 
Battle varied teams on your way to PLATINUM!
63.193:
The teams whose League Score ranks in the top 96 can 
progress to the Extra Stage! This is composed of 12 races 
per block, for <color=#ff9900>24 races</color> total. Umamusume entering these 
races are granted the <color=#ff9900>SUPER HERO</color> epithet! 
※Participation can be set in the options
63.194: In the Extra Stage you can cheer for an Umamusume \nby hitting the <color=#ff9900>"Neighce!"</color> button once per race. \nDoing so grants you some neighce rewards.
63.195:
In each block, the <color=#ff9900>11th race is the Main Race</color>. 
In A block this will be raced by the top 4 teams, 
in B block the 5th–8th placed ones. Watching the 
Main Race grants rewards. All 24 races can also 
be watched with the focus on 1 Umamusume.
63.196:
Through Special Transfer you can <color=#ff9901>obtain gifts for transferring 
your trained Umamusume to another trainer's team</color>. 
Be aware you can't get Umamusume back once transferred! 
Ads are updated <color=#ff9901>every monday at 5:00</color>.
63.197: Each team has its own expectations. These not only come with \n<color=#ff9901>different rewards</color>, but <color=#ff9901>the higher the expectations, the more \nluxurious the rewards</color> for transferring your Umamusume to them.
63.198: Teams with high expectations will reward a piece of the \ntransferred <color=#ff9901>Hall of Fame Umamusume</color> as a thank you gift.
63.199: Only Circle Leaders can change the <color=#ff9901>Circle Card</color>. \nCircle info, comments, and images can be added \nand customized to show the appeal of your circle!
63.200:
Now you can play the crane game from training 
whenever you like. Aim for your favourite <color=#ff9900>Umamusume 
plushies (Paka-Puchi)</color> and view them in your collection! 
Catch them all and <color=#ff9900>complete the set</color>!
63.201:
In this scenario Umamusume replace their individual goals with 
the shared goal of conquering the <color=#ff9900>Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe</color>! 
An opportunity to do so appears <color=#ff9900>once during the classic and 
senior year each</color>. Work hard and chase your dreams with the 
other Project L'Arc members to triumph at the arc!
63.202:
Finishing graded races in the money and SS Matches with L'Arc 
members gets you <color=#ff9900>Supporter Pt</color> and increases <color=#ff9900>Fan Expectations</color>. 
Increased Expectations confers stat growth, a training bonus, 
and facility level ups to lead to further growth for your Umamusume!
63.203:
To unleash their true ability on foreign tracks it will 
be necessary to <color=#ff9900>gain or upgrade Foreign Aptitudes</color>. 
Obtain Foreign Aptitudes by fulfilling their requirements 
and level them up to <color=#ff9900>overcome challenges at Foreign Races</color>!
63.204:
<color=#ff9900>Interleague friendlies with foreign Umamusume</color> using VR at a virtual 
Longchamps are held 4 times during training. Like Foreign Races, 
these races <color=#ff9900>have challenges</color>. Supporter and Apt. Pt can be gained 
from them, so <color=#ff9900>raise those Foreign Aptitudes</color> and aim for victory!
63.205: You can <color=#ff9900>gain Foreign Aptitudes</color> through SS Matches \nand winning races. <color=#ff9900>The requirements for each vary</color> \nso check them out to gain as many as you can!
63.206:
The <color=#ff9900>Apt. Pt</color> gained through SS Matches and expeditions 
abroad can be used to <color=#ff9900>level up Foreign Aptitudes</color>! 
Leveling them up not only helps you overcome challenges 
but grants positive effects to aptitudes and bonuses in training. 
Gather Apt. Pt and level up aggressively!
63.207:
L'Arc members fill the <color=#ff9900>Star Gauge</color> through training and races, 
and <color=#ff9900>once it's full they can join an SS Match</color>! SS Matches will 
take up a turn, but can be held with <color=#ff9900>up to 5 participants</color>, granting 
Supporter Pt and stats! You might also find yourself in an even 
more powerful <color=#ff9900>SSS Match</color> at times.
63.208:
When winning an SS Match with L'Arc members, each member 
will <color=#ff9900>get a winning bonus</color>. Rewards are varied, including Skill Hints 
and Conditions, so take on the challenge of SS Matches once 
you get a few members together!
63.209:
From early July to early October an <color=#ff9900>Expedition Abroad</color> 
will have you undergo <color=#ff9900>special training</color> in France. 
<color=#ff9900>You can gain tons of Apt. Pt</color> while abroad so it is 
a great chance to level up Foreign Aptitudes!
63.210:
During the Expedition Abroad you will enter the <color=#ff9900>Prix Niel</color> 
and the <color=#ff9900>Prix Foy</color> in early September of the classic 
and senior years, respectively. These serve as trials 
for the <color=#ff9900>Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe</color> in early October!
63.211:
<color=#ff9900>Once per day</color> you can enter a <color=#ff9900>special race</color> after 10 scout races. 
These special races don't consume a ticket and are raced against 
special NPC teams. Winning this race earns you a large amount 
of Scout Pts.
63.212:
In the <color=#ff9901>Derby Stallion: Masters edition of Special Transfers</color> 
you can transfer your trained Umamusume to another trainer's 
team for rewards. Be aware that once you transfer someone, 
she will be gone and you will not be able to get her back.
63.213:
Each team has its own expectations. These not only come with 
<color=#ff9901>different rewards</color>, but <color=#ff9901>the higher the expectations, the more 
luxurious the rewards</color> for transferring your Umamusume to them. 
This time, even more luxurious <color=#ff9901>grade 4</color> rewards are available!
63.214: In the <color=#ff9901>Derby Stallion: Masters edition of Special Transfers </color> \nall transfers will also reward <color=#ff9901>pieces of the transferred Umamusume</color>. \nGather a lot of pieces to develop your Umamusume!
63.215: Each race comes in a number of LEVELs. \nWhen winning a race, the <color=#ff9901>next LEVEL</color> will unlock.
63.216: You will get a reward the <color=#ff9901>first time you finish first</color> in each LEVEL. \nWork hard, aim high!
63.217: Each Umamusume in your hall of fame \ncan only <color=#ff9901>participate three times</color>.
63.235:
Training with Umamusume organized as a <color=#ff9900>support card</color> will 
increase your <color=#ff9900>training efficiency and bond gauge</color>. When the 
bond gauge is full, <color=#ff9900>Friendship Training</color> can occur. You may <color=#ff9900>gain 
various benefits</color> if certain others watch you train as well.
63.236:
When a support card Umamusume has a <color=#ff9900>! mark</color> on her, grab your 
chance to <color=#ff9900>increase Hint Lv of one of this partner's skills</color> upon 
successfully completing the training session. This will confer 
a <color=#ff9900>discount on the Skill Pt needed to acquire the skill</color>.
63.237:
If you train your Umamusume when her <color=#ff9900>energy is low</color>, she may 
<color=#ff9900>fail the training</color> and her ability may not improve. There are 
<color=#ff9900>various disadvantages</color> to failing a training session, so always 
keep an eye on her <color=#ff9900>energy and failure rate</color>!
63.254:
You can check and set your trainer information. On your 
<color=#ff9900>birthday</color>, you will receive a congratulatory comment from Uma 
Musume on the home screen, and changing your <color=#ff9900>gender</color> will change 
some scenarios. (Gender can be changed at any time)
63.255:
You can set up a <color=#ff9900>representative Umamusume</color> and <color=#ff9900>support card</color> to 
help your followers in their training. You will earn <color=#ff9900>Friend Pt 
the next day</color> depending on the number of times you do this. 
(This will be given as a gift)
63.256:
You can select the representative Umamusume and support 
card of the friends you <color=#ff9900>follow</color> from each list in training. 
You also earn more Friend Pt by helping a <color=#ff9900>mutual follower</color> 
to train. If you don't have many followers, try looking 
in the <color=#ff9900>recommendations</color>.
63.257: You can check the items you currently have. You can also use \nconsumable items. Some items can be converted to Money. \n<color=#ff9900>Converting items cannot be undone</color>, so be careful.
63.249:
<color=#ff9900>Room Match</color> allows you to race against other trainers 
with your Hall of Fame Umamusume <color=#ff9900>Host</color>: Set your own 
conditions for the race <color=#ff9900>Join</color>: Join another trainer's 
race. <color=#ff9900>Watch</color>: Enter an ID to watch the race.
63.250:
The race held will be GI. There are two modes. <color=#ff9900>Simple Mode</color> 
allows you to hold a race right away. <color=#ff9900>Detailed mode</color> allows you 
to choose weather, participation conditions, etc. first. Up to 
<color=#ff9900>3 Umamusume per person</color> can be entered.
63.251:
Recruit participants for your races from the participation 
list. Trainers close to you can also be recruited using 
the <color=#ff9900>Circle and SNS Sharing functions</color>. For future reference, 
<color=#ff9900>you can save your favorite races</color>. Have a go organizing 
a race with your friends!
63.252: Save Umamusume in <color=#ff9900>My Entrants</color> to <color=#ff9900>select them easily</color> during \nregistration! You can also save them from the results screen.

69.8001: If you're not going fast during the last spurt, you might be lacking speed.
69.8002: If you're losing positions in the final stretch, you might be lacking stamina.
69.8003: If you find yourself unable to get ahead, it might be good to increase your power.
69.8004: If you find yourself unable to catch up in the final stretch, you might be lacking guts.
69.8005: With higher wisdom, positioning and skill activation becomes easier.
69.8006: If you're low on Money and Support Points, try entering the Daily Races.
69.8007: Upgrading your Support Cards and Umamusume is key to winning races.
69.8008: Race outcomes are not only decided by what happens during the race, but also the weather and sometimes even luck...
69.8009: Upgrading the level of your Support Cards will give you better support effects.
69.8010: Limit Breaking your Support Cards will give you powerful support effects.
69.8011: The effect [Motivation Bonus] also amplifies negative effects, so be careful!
69.8012: The effect [Friendship Bonus] increases the effect of Friendship Training.

88.20070:
— Mom? Hi! It's been a while, how are you? 
— Me? I just finished lunch with Chev and Viv. 
— As usual, Cheval's was all brown and Vivlos 
won't eat anything she doesn't find interesting. 
Really, what am I to do with these two! 
— Oh, but don't worry. I made sure they got their veggies 
and rice. I can get Viv with rewards as always, and Chev… 
I just have to chase her and feed her myself, y'know? 
— Heheh. Aw, it's no problem at all. 
I'm totally used to it. Besides… 
— You know how it is, mama. I love looking after these two.
88.20071:
"—— Her racing heart skips a beat as if responding in joy. 
Right at the final corner's exit, Royce's ears picked up 
the voices of those dear to her with certainty." 

(I can see the image floating in Royce's mind clear as day… 
it tells me this is where I accompany her in pianissimo… 
a vital respite before the climax)  

"«Go for it, Royce!», they shout. 
Hesitation no longer inhabited Royce's heart."  

(Thus we enter the bridge! Just what I was waiting on! 
Playing the main theme in slow tempo! Grandioso!)  

"The sounds of feet digging into the earth. 
A moment later, the packed crowd witnesses 
a streak of light traversing the straight ——"  

"… Perfect! The climax had the ubiquitous strength 
I imagined to it… one of classic youthful passion, 
awakened by the bonds woven up to that point… 
And Earth… you provided the most 
wonderful sonic backdrop to it!"  

"You flatter, the notes stirred my soul 
and I simply had to join in! 
A lovely melody was the natural result. 
It is I who wishes to offer thanks, Ms. Royce!"
88.30172:

88.30174:
Tonight is the "Mejiro's Christmas Night"… 
A special event on a special night, held by the Mejiro 
Umamusume for their unfailingly supportive fans. 
"W-welcome to the Mejiro's Christmas Night! 
Please check in over here!" 
"Huh… you want a picture with me…!? 
…… O-Okay, I can do that……… C-Cheese!" 
That's why Dober, always so tense around others, was 
mustering all her courage to interact with the guests. 
"You're doing great, Dober… Your buccinator is still 
looking tight, but you're welcoming guests magnificently!" 
When I first started secretly looking out for her, I was 
worried she might be having a tough time… but it seems 
that there we no need for me to leave my post…… 
"Oh, what a wonderful night… to be given 
such a present by the Mejiros this year…" 
"… We all put a lot of effort into tonight, hoping that 
everyone would enjoy a wonderful christmas. It would 
make us all very pleased if you came away with some 
great memories." 
Even with ladies she has never met, she manages to 
converse in her own words, without drawing back. 
…… Before long, my zygomaticus major had relaxed 
quite a bit. That's right. Dober had always been like this. 
She always puts a brave step forwards when acting 
for someone, when helping others. 
She's a kind girl like that. 
"… Do your best, Dober!"
88.30175:
"Ms. Ramonu. Lunch has been served. ……Ms. Ramonu?" 
…… No response to my knocking either. 
Fully aware of my ill manner, I opened the door 
to the lounge. Ms. Ramonu was painting. 
It was an image I could not understand —— 
An abstract painting beyond the comprehension of others. 
I had heard about this from another maid. 
There had been a time when Ms. Ramonu's legs were weak, 
and she didn't partake in training during the winter. 
She had spent that time painting abstract images. 
Her fervor, her adulation, her passion, her melancholy —— 
She threw them all at the canvas. Her art, much like herself, 
was imbued with indescribable beauty. 
But why, why has she, at this point, taken up 
her brush once again? 
"… It falls far short of those times. But of course. 
These days, I can come face to face with my love." 
…… My breath was taken away even though I couldn't 
make sense of her words. Without knowing what had 
overcome her, I simply kept gazing at her beauty. 
"The snow has ceased. Let us talk of love.", I heard 
her murmur as I quietly vacated the room. 
…… All that would remain of our meeting was the work 
I hadn't finished, and the white canvas upon which 
she had painted the lushest of greenery.
88.30176:
On a certain day nearing Christmas —— 
"Mmm, it's tough to decide when faced with 
such a large variety of choices～" 
"Indeed… Ryan would likely be happy with 
anything, but… it's always nicer to find something 
that she would truly enjoy, isn't it?" 
"What do you think about horseshoes～? 
My dear sister Ryan patiently accompanied me 
in selecting a pair in the past～" 
"Therefore, I would like to take some time to carefully 
pick out a pair of horseshoes for her this time." 
"I see. So she waited patiently for Bright to decide which 
ones she wanted… Hehe, that's so like Ryan." 
"… I remember, when I was little, she held my hand on 
a stormy night full of thunder. Even though she disliked 
staying up late, she stayed with me the whole night…… 
I always thought I couldn't compare to that." 
"What'd be a good way to repay her… maybe something 
for good sleep? But I'm pretty sure she sleeps well as is…" 
"The store will be closing in 30 minutes. 
We look forward to you next visit." 
"Whoah, it's that time already?!" 
…… Uhhh, What do I do… I'm having a harder 
time picking something than I expected…" 
"That's perfectly fine, Dober. 
You must take your time in expressing gratitude, 
otherwise your feelings might not reach～" 
"…… Heh. Bright could be very right. 
Well, let's come look around more tomorrow then."
88.30177:
Vivlos sets off running. 
The media folk gathered were not done 
asking questions, but quickly realizing 
she could not stand motionless in this moment, 
a wry smile simply formed on their faces. 
Though she must be incredibly tired, the reason 
her steps were light as a feather nonetheless 
could be seen at the end of her gaze.  

"Heey, siiiis～～～! First! 
I came first! I really did it!"  

There was Verxina, meeting her guileless little sister 
running straight at her, no eye for anything else, 
with open arms and an emotional expression.  

"Vivlos… thank you…! 
You ran an incredible, fantastic final leg. 
Those 7cm I couldn't close… 
The things I couldn't see behind them… 
You revealed them to me today."  

"Ehehe～ I have a second stomach for compliments～～♪"  

"… While I still thought of you as my cute, 
needy little sister, somewhere along you've 
become so strong."  

"Well my older sister's well known for her spirit, 
so of course I'll win if I set my thoughts on it! 
Ah, but even so, I'll always be a cute little sister♡"  

"Hahahah, I guess so. I'd love to see you 
being cute and strong out there."  

"Yeah! I'm gonna go win a lot! 
In huge races, or against powerful opponents! 
And I'll always come back for your compliments♪ 
What do you think? Deal?♡"
88.30178:
"Duramente drifts far to the outside! 
A mistake likely to cost her dear!!" 
 
I can hear the roars of the crowd between 
that of the wind rushing past my ears. 
I feel removed from my body, like it is not my own. 
 
(Have I lost my composure...?!) 
 
No, it's not that. It's not nerves sending shivers 
through me, but something deep inside, an urge —— 
 
"Haaaaaaaaaaah!!" 
 
"Duramente from the outside! Can you believe it, 
Duramente has found a way from the outside!!" 
 
That's right... it's the urge in my blood, the pride 
within its line. It stimulates me, encouraging, 
emboldening, to prove that I am the "strongest". 
 
"Is this what she is capable of!? Duramente!!"
88.30179:
Hanachōzu; floating flowers in a Shinto ablution basin. 
Spectacular colors adorning a new year still far 
from springtime's blossoming buds. 
Both of us momentarily taken by their beauty. 
Our wishes are like buds waiting to open — those were 
the words softly leaving your lips. To let them bloom. 
 
For each of the numerous flowers laying within 
the basin, so too a wish lay within me. 
Plip-plop, plip-plop. One by one, droplets fell 
underneath this branch of the Satono tree, 
drawing expanding rings upon the water's surface. 
I am reminded of drops from days past, drops which 
followed the curves of my cheeks. 
The pile of unflowering flowers. 
 
I'll let them blossom this time, on the most 
floriferous once in a lifetime stage. 
I'll let these flowers — these wishes — reach full bloom, 
like this beautiful hanachōzu. 
 
"Yeah. We'll have them blooming, without fail." 
You nodded your head, with a smile as warm as 
the sunlight stretching over the buds.
88.30180:
Umamusume — taking on names of another world, 
succeeding their corresponding spirit and accompanying 
histories, both brilliant and tragic, they are born to run. 
Through their many races, these girls eventually 
become part of history themselves. 
 
"I'll be Japan's number one Umamusume!" 
A vow made to her two mothers. Harboring her 
ambition to be "Japan's number one", a girl leaving behind 
her hometown encounters rivals, competes with them 
in races, and through her victories and defeats eventually 
turns that dream of hers into reality. 
 
"I'll win regardless." 
A "sovereign" chasing after the "emperor". 
Spurred by an unyielding spirit, she fought through 
repeated setbacks to accomplish miracles in front of 
the friends who always ran by her side and the rival 
who supported her all the way. 
 
"Everyone said they want to see me run..." 
A young girl in awe of the unbreakable "sovereign". 
Together with her bosom friend with whom she exchanged 
a promise, she jumped into the world of racing. 
Though beset by doubt in her own dream, she managed 
to find herself, becoming a festival girl beloved by all. 
 
All said —— 
"Ah, over here, Spe!" 
"Wooh, I made it~! My battle meal was 
more delicious than I anticipated..." 
"Geez~ The race is about to start! 
—— Ah, I know! Why don't we race to the paddock? 
We can establish which one of us is number one♪" 
"Oh, that sounds fun! Wanna have a go at it, Spe?" 
"Of course! I might have arrived last, 
but I'm gonna finish first~!" 
"Okaay, get ready... go!!" 
The road they travel has not yet reached its end.

120.1: With an outrageous declaration, young academy chairwoman Akikawa establishes a new race named the <color=#FF6D26>URA Finals</color>! Trainers and Umamusume work hand in hand to become its maiden champion!
120.2: Team up! A new experience awaits! …So began the sudden new team battle — <color=#FF6D26>Aoharu Hai</color>. But before the fun can start the academy faces a crisis!? Stand united and claim victory to save the freedoms of Tracen Academy!
120.3: Why do Umamusume sing at lives? A producer suddenly appears to propose a new plan — the <color=#FF6D26>Grand Live</color>. Umamusume face their lives from a different perspective,and the answers they reach are—!
120.4: A new race established by the media — <color=#FF6D26>Twinkle Star Climax</color>. A battle to determine the strongest! Run towards your own climax, chasing your dreams!
120.5: A support AI carrying the names of the 3 goddesses is the newest development to confront trainers in their quest to support their Umamusume with all they have. Through the wisdom imparted this way, they now aim to reach new heights in the <color=#FF6D26>Grand Masters</color>.
120.6: Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe, the peak of international racing. Those who seek their victory at the top of the world every year. <color=#FF6D26>Project L'Arc</color>, newly established at Tracen Academy. The curtain rises on a wistful journey of chasing dreams.

128.1044: Become the top umadol! Euphoria, cuteness, and poppy on the mic!♪ Smile wide and sing along☆
128.1055: Lookie there! That a ship?! A UFO!? Nein, it's Golshi!!! Peace Peace♪ Howboutthat? All your base are belong to me☆
128.1056: A solemn chorus sung by the Mejiro family. Their splendor reaches far and wide—

169.1012: She's the youngest child, but has a mother's touch.
169.1014: She grew up with a hawk named Mambo. He's like her sibling.
169.1015: She respects her parents for raising her to be gorgeous.
169.1016: Her parents and sister always say "taciturnity is a sign of kindness".
169.1017: Her parents taught her Imperialism from a young age.
169.1018: She spends all year meticulously planning her mother's birthday party.
169.1019: My family's hobbies include: Camping! Festivals! BBQ!
169.1020: When she goes home, she goes fishing with her grandfather and his fishing buddies.
169.1021: When she's with her brothers and sisters, she's called "Tama-nee".
169.1022: She's better at taking care of her uninhibited and open-minded sister than her parents are.
169.1023: Her mother and her sister used to have matching hairstyles.
169.1024: Her father was a pilot, so the airport was her playground.
169.1025: Her family loves coffee, so their beans are specially imported.
169.1026: Her family is living in an old-fashioned home because of the frequent breakage of household appliances.
169.1027: Her father is very young and is often mistaken for her brother.
169.1028: Her father is a master chef, and her mother is a baking teacher.
169.1030: She used to fall asleep listening to her parents read picture books.
169.1032: The unorthodox child of a family with a spectacular reputation in the racing world.
169.1033: They prepare two birthday cakes every year.
169.1035: Watching the Derby together is the most important family event of all.
169.1037: They run a cake shop, and their specialty is baumkuchen.
169.1038: They missed their daughter so much that they applied to be members of Tracen Academy's staff.
169.1039: They always picked out cute and durable clothes for her.
169.1040: Her mother has clear skin, and her father is a brilliant blonde.
169.1041: Her family's motto is "Praise, praise, praise, and praise!".
169.1045: Her family's day-care center has a reputation for making people feel at home.
169.1046: Her hair ornament is from the first idol costume that her mother made.
169.1048: Her parents always told her to eat her veggies first. That always made her the most upset.
169.1050: Rumor has it that the moms of BNW are friends now.
169.1052: Her favorite dish is her mother's carrot rice.
169.1054: Sunday mornings are Tokusatsu time with the whole family!
169.1062: Whenever she goes home, her parents hang a banner at their restaurant.
169.1063: She tends to lead family meetings.
169.1080: She tries to avoid her parents on social media.
169.1082: She often chats with her older sister at family meet-ups.
169.1091: Their father's hamburg steaks are a staple at family gatherings.
169.1094: She can't get over the fact that her older brother is popular with the girls.
169.1102: They tend to chat through jam sessions.
169.1108: Her family gets serious in table tennis matches at hot spring vacations.
169.1109: They often go picnicking when they're together.
169.1116: She's been taken up Mt. Fuji to the third station at 3 years old, the 5th station at 5 and to the top at 7.
169.1119: Not a day goes by that she doesn't think about them.
169.1120: She can tell what her parents are thinking about from their facial expressions alone.
169.1110: Her mother has a secret recipe for carrot glacé.
169.1121: Who gets to do house chores is decided through games of "Acchi Muite Hoi".
169.1124: They all have a refined sweet smell.
